Theory. 

Explanation: The paper discusses the application of an Exclusive-Sum-Of-Products (ESOP) minimizer in machine learning and pattern theory. It analyzes various logic synthesis programs and proposes improvements for strongly unspecified functions. While the paper does touch on practical problems in application areas, it primarily focuses on the theoretical aspects of Boolean minimization for machine learning. Therefore, the paper belongs to the Theory sub-category of AI.
